<ul>
<li>For a small sampling of some of the letters and statements see: Wikiquote: <a href="http://en.wikiquote.org/wiki/Philippine-American_War#American_Torture_and_Attrocities_against_Filipinos" class="external text" title="http://en.wikiquote.org/wiki/Philippine-American_War#American_Torture_and_Attrocities_against_Filipinos" rel="nofollow">American Torture and Attrocities against Filipinos</a>, Wikisource: <a href="http://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Secretary_Root%27s_Record:%22Marked_Severities%22_in_Philippine_Warfare" class="extiw" title="s:Secretary Root's Record:&quot;Marked Severities&quot; in Philippine Warfare">Anti-Imperalist summary of the findings of the Lodge Committee</a>, Wikipedia: <a href="/wiki/Lodge_Committee" title="Lodge Committee" class="mw-redirect">Lodge Committee</a>, particularly the testiony of: <a href="/wiki/Lodge_committee#Sergeant_Charles_S._Riley_.28_A.29" title="Lodge committee" class="mw-redirect">Charles S. Riley</a>, <a href="/wiki/Lodge_Committee#Private_William_L_Smith_.28_A.29" title="Lodge Committee" class="mw-redirect">Private William L Smith</a>, <a href="/wiki/Lodge_Committee#Sergeant_Edward_J._Davis_.28_A.29" title="Lodge Committee" class="mw-redirect">Sergeant Edward J. Davis</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Lodge_Committee#ex-Corporal_Richard_Thomas_O.27Brien_.28_A.29" title="Lodge Committee" class="mw-redirect">ex-Corporal Richard Thomas O'Brien</a></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-72"><b><a href="#cite_ref-72" title="">^</a></b> <a href="/wiki/New_York_Sun" title="New York Sun" class="mw-redirect">New York Sun</a> March 10, 1902; p.&#160;234–235. In 1902 Funston toured the United States speaking to increase public support for the war in the Philippines. He said: “I personally strung up thirty-five Filipinos without trial, so what was all the fuss over Waller's ‘dispatching’ a few ‘treacherous savages’? If there had been more <a href="/wiki/Jacob_H._Smith" title="Jacob H. Smith">Smiths</a> and <a href="/wiki/Littleton_Waller" title="Littleton Waller">Wallers</a>, the war would have been over long ago. Impromptu domestic hanging might also hasten the end of the war. For starters, all Americans who had recently petitioned Congress to sue for peace in the Philippines should be dragged out of their homes and lynched."— Colonel Frederick Funston at a banquet in Chicago.</li>
<li id="cite_note-73"><b><a href="#cite_ref-73" title="">^</a></b> <a href="#CITEREFMiller1982" title="">Miller 1982</a>, p.&#160;89;* <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFStorey.2C_Moorfield_and_Codman.2C_Julian">Storey, Moorfield and Codman, Julian. "<a href="http://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Secretary_Root%27s_Record:%22Marked_Severities%22_in_Philippine_Warfare#How_Charges_Were_Investigated" class="external text" title="http://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Secretary_Root%27s_Record:%22Marked_Severities%22_in_Philippine_Warfare#How_Charges_Were_Investigated" rel="nofollow">Secretary Root's Record: “Marked Severities” in Philippine Warfare</a>". <i>Philippine Investigating Committee</i>: 12–15<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Secretary_Root%27s_Record:%22Marked_Severities%22_in_Philippine_Warfare#How_Charges_Were_Investigated" class="external free" title="http://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Secretary_Root%27s_Record:%22Marked_Severities%22_in_Philippine_Warfare#How_Charges_Were_Investigated" rel="nofollow">http://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Secretary_Root%27s_Record:%22Marked_Severities%22_in_Philippine_Warfare#How_Charges_Were_Investigated</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Secretary+Root%27s+Record%3A+%E2%80%9CMarked+Severities%E2%80%9D+in+Philippine+Warfare&amp;rft.jtitle=Philippine+Investigating+Committee&amp;rft.aulast=Storey%2C+Moorfield+and+Codman%2C+Julian&amp;rft.au=Storey%2C+Moorfield+and+Codman%2C+Julian&amp;rft.pages=12%E2%80%9315&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fen.wikisource.org%2Fwiki%2FSecretary_Root%2527s_Record%3A%2522Marked_Severities%2522_in_Philippine_Warfare%23How_Charges_Were_Investigated&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Philippine-American_War"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
